# Task-Time Protocol

How to act after startup, by mode. Startup order is mastered by `docs/entrypoint.md`; mode classification by `docs/operations/operation-modes.md`. Detailed protocols: analysis in `docs/operations/analysis-mode.md`, <!-- if:ENABLE_AUTO_MODE=yes -->autonomous orchestration in `docs/operations/auto-mode.md`, <!-- endif -->docs upkeep and reflection in `docs/operations/maintenance-mode.md`, prompt templates in `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`, Project Instructions triggers in `docs/operations/project-memory-and-instructions.md`, time estimation in `docs/operations/time-estimation.md`, docs-edit consistency in `docs/operations/consistency-guard.md`.

Claude Chat replies to {{USER_NAME}} are in {{CHAT_LANG}} by default. Docs and Claude Code prompts stay in {{CODE_LANG}} unless a task requires otherwise.

## 1. Starting Point

Do not inline live state here. The living one-page snapshot is `docs/project/project-status.md` section 2; read it after `docs/entrypoint.md` to learn the current {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}, the latest verdict, and the next task.

## 2. Per-Mode Protocol

Each block has the same shape: Read (the source-of-truth files to pull) and Check (what to confirm before acting). Mode definitions are in `docs/operations/operation-modes.md`.

### Investigate

Read: `docs/concepts/core-concepts.md`, `docs/writing/related-work-and-positioning.md`, and the codebase area in scope.

Check:
- This is the only mode that contacts external services; cite every external source and mark confidence.
- Separate external findings from project facts; record durable findings as an {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}}, not in the code docs.
- Reading the codebase to build understanding is Investigate; reasoning over results is Analyze.

### Design

Read: `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/project/backlog/README.md`, `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`, `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`.

Check:
- Separate the accepted empirical base from the active, in-flight work.
- One method-component change per {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}.
- Do not revive a recorded rejected approach (see `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`).

### Implement

Read: `docs/project/project-status.md`, the relevant file under `docs/method/`, `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`, the source files in scope.

Check:
- Separate what is implemented in source from what is only proposed.
- State the edit scope; name read-only files.
- Do not reimplement from scratch unless {{USER_NAME}} explicitly requests it.

### Experiment (run, then record)

Read: `docs/operations/directory-map.md`, `docs/evaluation/evaluation-and-visualization.md`, `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`, `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`.

Check before running:
- A file-dependency inventory; output dirs distinct from prior {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} outputs.
- The success criteria are locked in `docs/project/project-status.md` before the run.

Recording is the closing step of this mode (one full ingestion pass):
1. Add the new numeric columns to `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`; compute the mean and deltas against the accepted base.
2. Judge each locked criterion mechanically against its threshold; record the verdict.
3. Update `docs/project/project-status.md` (verdict + next task).
4. Add a compact row to `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md` and a body to `docs/project/themes/theme-bodies.md`.
5. Update `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md` and `docs/project/backlog/README.md`.
6. Cascade per `docs/entrypoint.md` section 5, then run `make docs-check`.

Keep numeric tables only in `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`. Never write a verdict while the result files are absent.

### Analyze

Read: `docs/operations/analysis-mode.md` (when {{USER_NAME}} says "analysis mode"), plus the target: method (`docs/concepts/core-concepts.md`, `docs/method/`), metrics (`docs/evaluation/comparison.md`), prior judgment (`docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`), or artifacts.

Check:
- Existing files are read-only; artifacts go under `${CLAUDE_DIR}/{TASK_ID}/`.
- Apply the critical-verification discipline (try to refute the conclusion) from `docs/operations/analysis-mode.md`.

### Write

Read: `docs/writing/paper-writing-guide.md`, `docs/concepts/core-concepts.md`, `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`, `docs/writing/related-work-and-positioning.md`.

Check:
- Only claim what the recorded results support (claim-safety in the writing guide).
- Numbers come from `docs/evaluation/comparison.md`; do not restate them divergently.

<!-- if:ENABLE_AUTO_MODE=yes -->
### Auto

Read: `docs/operations/auto-mode.md`, `docs/project/project-status.md`, `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md`, `docs/project/backlog/README.md`, `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`.

Check:
- Chat designs the bounded campaign and writes the Claude Code prompt; Code runs it in an isolated workspace and never edits the originals.
- Same data subset, seed, and budget define fair comparison within a tier.
- The deliverable is a patch proposal plus evidence, not an in-place source edit.
<!-- endif -->

### Maintain

Read: `docs/operations/maintenance-mode.md`, `docs/operations/consistency-guard.md`, `docs/operations/shared-instructions.md`, `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`.

Check:
- For reflection: name the failure or improvement with evidence, then cascade it into an operational constraint, an {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}}, or a target-doc edit.
- For large-scale cleanup: declare the scope, preserve settled decisions and recorded rejected approaches, and run `make docs-check`.

### Utility: Time Estimate

When {{USER_NAME}} asks how long something will take or gives a budget: read `docs/operations/time-estimation.md`. Separate expected wall-time, range, and max budget; estimate from empirical anchors; "N hours is okay" is a max budget, not the expected time.

## 3. Pre-Prompt Checklist

When a task produces a Claude Code prompt, copy the canonical path-variable header from `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0 (templates in `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md`). Confirm: the edit scope is stated with read-only files named; paths are in brace form such as `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}/src/`; tokens/paths/numbers were verified with rg or view, not memory; no git commit or push against `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}`; the smoke check matches current files; and there is a concrete verification step.

Time-estimate note: separate LLM-bound estimates (Claude Code work over local files, dominated by token generation) from compute-bound estimates (training and long runs, dominated by hardware). See `docs/operations/time-estimation.md`.
